    "( 1) can be written as a 2D TN, which we contract efficiently in the thermodynamic limit using anisotropic CTMRG [73,74].",
    "To capture Z 2 nematic order, we use a 4 × 4 unit cell (see [70]).Alternatively, we analyze an equivalent model on the dual lattice by placing spins on bonds: σ (i,x):= (-1) ix+iy (θ i+x -θ i) and σ (i,ŷ):= (-1) ix+iy (θ i -θ i+ŷ) [30,35].",
    "The dual Hamiltonian becomesH D = -J 1 b cos σ b + J 2 2 ⟨b,b ′ ⟩ cos(σ b + σ b ′),(2)with the local constraint cos(σ(i,x) + σ (i,ŷ) + σ (i+x,ŷ) + σ (i+ŷ,x)) = 1 at each site-index i.The bond variables σ b take values that are even multiples of π/q, as before.",
    "This dual representation simplifies the partition function [70], allowing efficient contraction via the original isotropic CTMRG algorithm [71,72] using a single-site unit cell.",
    "The phase diagram.-Figure 1(a) and (b) show the phase diagram for q = 6."
